  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to evaluate the incidence and risk factor of toxic maculopathy
      who treated with hydroxychloroquine or chloroquine due to their autoimmune disease such as
      rheumatoid arthritis or systemic lupus erythematosus. Total 5-year of the study periods, the
      investigators will screen these patients by baseline examination (Fundus photography, fundus
      autofluorescence, spectral-domain optical coherence tomography, Humphrey visual field test
      and multifocal electroretinography) and observe with same examination for every year.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
